summary: Oh! Killing Eve (on BBC iplayer currently) is so good - I’m a hoe for beautiful assassin women at the top of their game and...
body: Oh! Killing Eve (on BBC iplayer currently) is so good - I’m a hoe for beautiful assassin women at the top of their game and intuitive, self-sufficient detective women who are underestimated. If you enjoy those things and also lovely character development and great pacing alongside some pretty cinematography and insane locations: then you have got to watch it. I really enjoyed The Fall but it let me down so much, it couldn’t carry its own delirious, gritty momentum in the end and severely overused violence upon women as a way to evoke the audience. This series is kind of like The Fall in the intense dynamic between killer and the one trying to stop the killer, but it won’t let you down.

description:

I was trying to decide which video to include Eve’s or Villanelle’s? They both successfully show that both have a dark side. Though Villanelle is the more disturbing one because she seems to fall in the sociopathic spectrum.


The way Sandra puts it in 0:58 really pushes it again into Collateral territory 



What is it they are both yet to discover? Their truth?
